.TH JD-LS 1 2024-09-02 "jd @tag@"
.
.SH NAME
.
jd-ls \- list directories of the johnny.decimal system
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.
.SY jd-ls
.RB { " \-h " | " \-\-help " }
.YS
.SY jd-ls
.RI [ " <jd_path_descriptor> " ]
.YS
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.
.P
The \fBjd-ls\fR command can be used to list the contents of a directory in the
johnny.decimal system. It prints all files and subdirectories of said
johnny.decimal directory to stdout, omitting files and directories beginning
with a period (.). This behaviour can, however, be customised. See
\fBjd.conf\fR(5).
.
.SH OPTIONS
.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display a short help message.
.
.TP
.I <jd_path_descriptor>
List the contents of the directory with a specific johnny.decimal path
descriptor, i. e. either an area, category or id. To list the contents of an
area, specify the common first digit of its categories.
.IP
If this argument is omitted, the top-level johnny.decimal directory containing
the areas will be listed.
.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.
The \fBjd\fR utility exits > 0 if an error occurs, 0 otherwise.
.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.
.TP
.I JD_PATH
This environment variable can be used to override the configured file system
path to the johnny.decimal system. Simply set it to the desired path. Tilde
expansion is supported, \fI\(ti/johnny\fR for example would be an acceptable
value.
.
.TP
.I XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Path to the user-specific configuration directory. Defaults to
\fI\(ti/.config\fR. See \fIFILES\fR.
.
.SH FILES
.
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/jd/jd.conf
This is the main \fBjd\fR configuration file. See \fBjd.conf\fR(5).
.
.SH SEE ALSO
.
.nh
.BR jd-path "(1), " jd-config "(1), " jd-ls "(1), " jd.conf "(5)"
